nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.program

Class ProgramTranslator<TProgram,TOutput extends Output<TProgram>>

  • nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.program.ProgramTranslator<TProgram,TOutput>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Module

    public class ProgramTranslator<TProgram,TOutput extends Output<TProgram>>
implements Module

    Module that can be used to translate programs to external representations.

    This class primarily exists to make it easy to translate programs from a single place, rather than from internally defined logic.

    • Method Detail

      • translate

        @NotNull
public java.lang.String translate(@NotNull
                                           Program<TProgram,TOutput> program)

        Translates program from some internal representation to a concrete representation.

        This is useful for taking an evolved LGP program and translating it to an output that can be integrated into some other eco-system (e.g. the C programming language).

        Parameters:
        program - A program to translate.
